The 19th Flak Division, with sixteen {{nowrap|88 mm}} batteries and several {{nowrap|20 mm}} anti-aircraft batteries, was on the coast, the 1st Luftwaffe Brigade, little stronger than a battalion, was behind ''Giovani Fascisti'' and Africa Panzer Grenadier Regiment watched the main Gabès–Mareth road. These and the 164 Light Division, were the only mobile infantry groups available.

